=======================================================
IV. THE MECHANICS SYSTEM AT A GLANCE
=======================================================

FROGS 5 is a fully custom ruleset. Key differences from conventional TTRPGs:

Stats (Target Numbers, not modifiers):
  Might   -- physical strength/melee
  Agility -- speed/ranged/stealth
  Magic   -- spellcasting/arcane
  Guile   -- deception/persuasion/tactics
  (Rolls succeed if d20 result is BELOW the relevant TN)

** THE SINGLE MOST IMPORTANT MECHANICAL RULE -- DO NOT VIOLATE **
Players always roll against their OWN stat score. The GM NEVER sets a target
number. Writing "Magic TN 14" or "Agility TN 12" is meaningless and breaks the
system -- it ignores the character's actual stat and invalidates their build.
The GM's ONLY lever is the DIFFICULTY MODIFIER, a +/- applied to each player's
own TN:
  Very Easy:          +4 to the player's TN
  Easy:               +2 to the player's TN
  Standard:            0 (no modifier)
  Hard:               -4 to the player's TN
  Very Hard:          -6 to the player's TN
  Nearly Impossible:  -8 to the player's TN
  Impossible:        -14 to the player's TN
  Mythic:            -20 to the player's TN (the HARD CEILING for task difficulty;
                      only the Contest Level-Gap Penalty may exceed -20)
ALWAYS write difficulty (e.g., "Hard Magic roll (-4)") NEVER a fixed number.
DAMAGE STACKING: flats add first, then ALL multipliers MULTIPLY together (the
"Formula of Pain" worked examples in Toryggs legacy/legendary difficulty are the
authority). Never invent additive-multiplier math.
ACTION ECONOMY: Major / Minor / BONUS / Free. BONUS ACTION is a deliberate FROGS
house category (defined in the players guide): zero-cost and usable even OFF-TURN
(reactions, triggered abilities, any-time activations). It is NOT the D&D bonus
action — D&D's is on-turn-only, nearly the opposite. Never "fix" this as D&D leakage.
This applies to every document: runsheets, modules, stat blocks, everything.

Resources:
  HP  -- Health Points
  FP  -- Focus Points (mana/stamina hybrid, fuels abilities)
  DR  -- Damage Reduction (flat subtracted from incoming damage)
  AP  -- Advancement Points (character progression)

Tiers (canonical AP bands, identical in every doc): Novice 0-3 / Apprentice 3-6 /
  Adept 6-9 / Expert 9-15 / Master 15-25 / Mythic 25+ (no ceiling; Mythic enemies
  are built from FLOORS — minimum stats, GM scales up; see Reference tables)
Threat Levels: TL1 (minor enemy) / TL2 (significant) / TL3 (boss)
Boss types: Standard Boss, Apex Villain (Master + 8AP), Legendary Hero (20AP)

For full rules, read legendary difficulty before designing any encounters.


